{"award_age":90.0,"bio_image":"full\/8724da10e7e3680f3a2e2949674e501b27bc2e6b.jpg","category":"Economics","country":"Poland","date_of_birth":"1917-08-21T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":"2008-06-24T00:00:00.000Z","gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/a\/a0\/Leonid_Hurwicz.jpg\/225px-Leonid_Hurwicz.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Leonid_Hurwicz","mini_bio":"<p><b>Leonid \"Leo\" Hurwicz<\/b> (August 21, 1917 \u2013 June 24, 2008) was a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Polish-American\" title=\"Polish-American\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Polish-American<\/a> economist and mathematician, born in Moscow.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Leonid_Hurwicz#cite_note-1\"><span>[<\/span>1<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Leonid_Hurwicz#cite_note-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> He originated <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Incentive_compatibility\" title=\"Incentive compatibility\">incentive compatibility<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Mechanism_design\" title=\"Mechanism design\">mechanism design<\/a>, which show how desired outcomes are achieved in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Economics\" title=\"Economics\">economics<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Social_science\" title=\"Social science\">social science<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Political_science\" title=\"Political science\">political science<\/a>. Interactions of individuals and institutions, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Market_(economics)\" title=\"Market (economics)\">markets<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Trade\" title=\"Trade\">trade<\/a> are analyzed and understood today using the models Hurwicz developed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Lohr_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Leonid_Hurwicz#cite_note-Lohr-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> To date, Leonid Hurwicz is the oldest <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Laureate\" title=\"Nobel Laureate\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Nobel Laureate<\/a>, having received the prize at the age of 90.<\/p><p>Hurwicz was <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Regents%27_Professor\" title=\"Regents' Professor\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Regents' Professor<\/a> of Economics (<a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Emeritus\" title=\"Emeritus\">Emeritus<\/a>) at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_Minnesota\" title=\"University of Minnesota\">University of Minnesota<\/a>. He was among the first economists to recognize the value of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Game_theory\" title=\"Game theory\">game theory<\/a> and was a pioneer in its application.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Leonid_Hurwicz#cite_note-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Higgins_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Leonid_Hurwicz#cite_note-Higgins-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Hurwicz shared the 2007 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Memorial_Prize_in_Economic_Sciences\" title=\"Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences\">Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences<\/a> with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Eric_Maskin\" title=\"Eric Maskin\">Eric Maskin<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Roger_Myerson\" title=\"Roger Myerson\">Roger Myerson<\/a> for their work on mechanism design.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ohlin_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Leonid_Hurwicz#cite_note-Ohlin-6\"><span>[<\/span>6<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Leonid Hurwicz","place_of_birth":"Moscow ,  Russia","place_of_death":"Minneapolis, Minnesota ,  United States","text":"Leonid Hurwicz ,  born in then Russian Republic , Economics, 2007","year":2007.0}